            <pp id="text">I have always been passionate about empowering others with the
              tools and knowledge they need to improve their own situations. As
              someone who has founded a community organization to bring
              essential supplies and aid to homeless and displaced citizens, I
              have an acute understanding of poverty and the situations that
              cause it. Because of this I see the need for technology to be
              implemented in different ways to help break the cycle of poverty
              and empower others with financial and technological literacy. <br />
              <br />
              In college, I discovered my passion for computer programing and
              data analysis, and I have strived to make use of these new tools
              to become more effective in my work and in my method of thinking.
              I have recently used my skills in R and Python, to create
              a report in the levels of vaccinations of
              schools in Washington. Using the Data, my team determined what
              demographics and economic levels were highest at risk in terms of
              outbreaks at schools. This last summer, I completed an intensive bootcamp in web development and design,
               learning from top engineers at LinkedIn, Expensify, and Remind.<br /></pp>
